B: Useless Weapon, I mean erm.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Dead Absor,<br>
I was wondering if you could answer a question for me. The Reaver off the Statue of Rallos Zek (which if you havn't had the displeasure is a VERY tough 7 day spawn giant badboy) Ammong his other drops are the BP of eradication an amazing BP, swiftblade of zek (an amazing 1h weapon) Hammer of battle (also an amazing weapon) and the reaver.<br>
<br>
The Reaver is 36/40 and grants +12 to all saves. The problem is it is NOT a magic weapon. <br>
<br>
The other weapons listed are all magic, I was wondering if it is a bug that the reaver is not? I'm assuming it is as the mob that drops it is consistent with the stats of the weapon (as a magic weapon)<br>
<br>
Thank you for looking into this,<br>
<br>
Galidin</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This is not a bug. This is intentional.<br>
<br>
This is a good example of a situational weapon. It's a very good weapon, but one that you can't use all the time, thus creating a decision for the character about what equipment to use and even what equipment to carry as spares.<br>
<br>
Alan<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  I noticed that the last poster addressed his email to &quot;Dead Absor&quot;. My questions are: Are you really dead? When did you die? Have you been dead all along? Did it have anything to do with you eating that pie?<br>
And lastly, would The Reaver work against you, or are you INVULNERABLE?<br>
<br>
Meirn Sageth<br>
Xegony</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Answers:<br>
<br>
As far as the I.R.S. is concerned, yes, I'm dead.<br>
<br>
If I told you that, I'd have to kill me.<br>
<br>
Maybe… ex-girlfriends might have opinions on this…<br>
<br>
Pie is always good, never bad.<br>
<br>
The Reaver won't work against me, but only because I run away very fast.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  DrooId wrote:<br>
<br>
I read this and got a little chuckle out of it because while hunting in Velketor's Lab the other night a Drake Skull Helm dropped. 20AC, 4wis, 4int, 20 mana, WAR/CLR/PAL/SHD/BRD wearable. A nice item for a cleric who is maxed on wis already except for 1 thing, 25.0 wt. Someone in the group commented, &quot;have you noticed something about the loot we get lately?&quot;. Of course someone had some smart ass comment but the person who asked the question said, &quot;No, not that, it's that a lot of the gear we have been getting has nice stats, EXCEPT for 1 which goes and messes things up.&quot; Personally I like this. It makes people consider the benefits of using items with extra nice stats but some penalties. The helm wound up going to our warrior because although it looked awesome on our high elf cleric, she has no way to buff her own strength and would be constantly encumbered. Good job on making things not so cut and dry. I like it.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
<br>
Alan<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I think the idea of situational weapons is a great one, however, I just don't see how a sword that grants +12 to all saves (ie makes you tougher just by holding it) could NOT be magical. Psionically imbued perhaps?<br>
Just my two cents,<br>
<br>
Aillron Lifereaver</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Well, therein lies the problem.<br>
<br>
It might indeed be magical (though it could be argued that it isn't). But being magical and being magical in the way needed to hit creatures that are resistant to non-magical weapons isn't the same thing.<br>
<br>
Perhaps there is a magical gem of protection on the weapon, and otherwise it's not magical. So it can offer protection but still not be able to harm creatures that are immune to normal weapons.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, the denotation of 'magical' in EverQuest means both, or either… The two concepts are marked with one bit of data.<br>
<br>
In this case the weapon does indeed have some magical qualities, but the blade itself is not magical.<br>
<br>
Alan<br>
